---
title: Android wiring at construction time
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    box rgb(232, 240, 254) App code
        participant DI as App startup / DI graph
        participant Activity as MainActivity
    end
    box rgb(232, 245, 233) oauth-kmp library
        participant PKCEFlow as PKCEFlow (app singleton)
        participant Holder as CurrentActivityWebAuthSession (app singleton)
        participant Session as AndroidWebAuthSession (one per Activity)
    end
    box rgb(255, 243, 224) OS
        participant ARA as Activity Result API
    end

    DI->>Holder: CurrentActivityWebAuthSession()
    DI->>PKCEFlow: PKCEFlow(webAuthSessionFactory = holder.factory, …)
    PKCEFlow->>Holder: factory.create(::continueSignInWithCallbackOrError)
    Note over Holder: ★ captures completionHandler =<br/>PKCEFlow::continueSignInWithCallbackOrError —<br/>the return path exists before any sign-in starts
    Holder-->>PKCEFlow: returns itself, so PKCEFlow.webAuthSession = holder
    Activity->>Holder: onCreate — bindTo(this)
    Holder->>Session: AndroidWebAuthSession(activity, completionHandler)
    Session->>ARA: AuthTabIntent.registerActivityResultLauncher(activity, callback)
    Note over Session, ARA: ★ must happen before the Activity is STARTED — the OS matches redelivered<br/>results to launchers by registration order, so every (re)creation must<br/>register the same launchers in the same order
    Note over Holder: delegate = session — a lifecycle observer keeps the binding on the foreground<br/>Activity (onResume reclaims it, onDestroy releases it only if still the owner)
